benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/customFields - Retrieve invoice item custom fields

covered: Valid Request: Successful GET scenarios with valid invoiceItemId and with default and explicit audit parameter values (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC05, TC13, TC14).
Empty Response: Retrieval returns an empty JSON array for items with no custom fields (TC04).
Query Parameters: Comprehensive coverage of audit parameter variations (NONE, FULL, MINIMAL), ignoring extraneous parameters (TC11), and handling of invalid audit values (TC19).

Error Handling: Coverage for invalid input formats (TC06, TC10, TC21), non-existent items (TC07), missing/invalid path (TC18), unauthorized access (TC08), system/dependency failures (TC09, TC20), and timeout scenarios (TC16).
Security/Input Validation: Protection against injection and XSS in invoiceItemId (TC10, TC21).
Performance/Scale: Large datasets (TC12) and concurrent requests (TC15) with performance considerations, plus timeout behavior (TC16).
Backward Compatibility/Regression: Backward compatibility with older Accept header (TC14) and regression check for missing audit parameter (TC13).
Accessibility: Ensures machine-readable JSON structure and descriptive field names (TC22).
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover pagination parameters (page, per_page) or related pagination semantics for large datasets.
Rate Limiting: No tests for throttling or 429 responses under bursty traffic.
Caching Behavior: No tests for caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) or 304 responses.
Authorization: Only 401 is tested; no explicit 403/token-expiry scenarios beyond 401.
Internal Server Error: No explicit 500 Internal Server Error path; only 503 in several cases.
recommendations: Add pagination tests (page and per_page) and verify pagination metadata/behavior when listing many custom fields.
Add rate-limiting tests (429) and throttle behavior under bursty traffic.
Add caching tests (ETag/Cache-Control) and 304/304-like behavior to ensure proper caching semantics.
Add 403 Forbidden tests for insufficient permissions and scenarios of token expiry or revocation.
Add explicit 500 Internal Server Error tests to differentiate from 503 Service Unavailable, ensuring proper error handling for DB or service failures.
Extend Accept header edge-case testing to cover additional legacy/compatibility scenarios and invalid content types.
